{"word":"νυμφεῖος","slug":"νυμφεῖος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νυμφεῖος</b></el> <el>(νυμφεῖος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νύμφη'><el>νύμφη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of a bride, bridal, nuptial</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>,<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><el>νυμφεῖον</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>δῶμα</el>), <i>the bridechamber</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>νυμφεῖα</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>ἱερά</el>), <el>τά</el>, <i>nuptial rites, marriage</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><el>νυμφεῖα τοῦ σαυτοῦ τέκνου</el> thine own son's <i>bride</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}